column15: The zona pellucida was removed using acid Tyrode’s solution and embryos were washed in M2. Dissociation was performed by incubating embryos in TrypLE (Life Technologies) for 3-6 minutes at 37°C followed by pipetting through fine pulled glass capillaries. Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.
column17: Cells were directly dispensed in lysis buffer and cDNA libraries were generated using Smart-seq2 as previously described (Picelli et al., 2013, 2014, Petropoulos et al., 2016).
column20: Sequenced reads were trimmed for adaptor sequence, and masked for low-complexity or low-quality sequence, then mapped to mm10 whole genome using STAR
column21: Data was processed using in house pipeline rpkmforgene.py (Ramsköld D et al., 2009)
column23: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text files include RPKM values and counts for each sample

column15: The zona pellucida was removed using acid Tyrode’s solution and embryos were washed in M2. Dissociation was performed by incubating embryos in TrypLE (Life Technologies) for 3-6 minutes at 37°C followed by pipetting through fine pulled glass capillaries. Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.

Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.

Dissociation was performed by incubating embryos in TrypLE (Life Technologies) for 3-6 minutes at 37°C followed by pipetting through fine pulled glass capillaries. Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.
column17: Cells were directly dispensed in lysis buffer and cDNA libraries were generated using Smart-seq2 as previously described (Picelli et al., 2013, 2014, Petropoulos et al., 2016).

column21: Data was processed using in house pipeline rpkmforgene.py (Ramsköld D et al., 2009)

column15: The zona pellucida was removed using acid Tyrode’s solution and embryos were washed in M2. Dissociation was performed by incubating embryos in TrypLE (Life Technologies) for 3-6 minutes at 37°C followed by pipetting through fine pulled glass capillaries. Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.

Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.
column17: Cells were directly dispensed in lysis buffer and cDNA libraries were generated using Smart-seq2 as previously described (Picelli et al., 2013, 2014, Petropoulos et al., 2016).
column20: Sequenced reads were trimmed for adaptor sequence, and masked for low-complexity or low-quality sequence, then mapped to mm10 whole genome using STAR
column21: Data was processed using in house pipeline rpkmforgene.py (Ramsköld D et al., 2009)
column23: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text files include RPKM values and counts for each sample

column15: The zona pellucida was removed using acid Tyrode’s solution and embryos were washed in M2. Dissociation was performed by incubating embryos in TrypLE (Life Technologies) for 3-6 minutes at 37°C followed by pipetting through fine pulled glass capillaries. Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.

column15: The zona pellucida was removed using acid Tyrode’s solution and embryos were washed in M2. Dissociation was performed by incubating embryos in TrypLE (Life Technologies) for 3-6 minutes at 37°C followed by pipetting through fine pulled glass capillaries. Individual cells were picked, aligned in rows in M2 media under oil and imaged using a Zeiss Axiovert 200 inverted microscope equipped with a Hamamatsu C9100-13 EM-CCD camera, a Quorum spinning disk confocal scan head and Volocity aquisition software (Perkin Elmer, version 6.3.1) Cdx2-eGFP was quantified by taking single plain images of individual cells, focusing on the plain with maximum eGFP intensity. Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.

Average nuclear Cdx2-eGFP measurements were corrected for cytoplasmic background. The cut off between “Cdx2-eGFP low” and “Cdx2-eGFP high” was set at 500 fluorescent intensity units and was based on the clearly distinct Cdx2-eGFP low cell population at the 64-cell and >64-cell stages.
